- The new study shows that playing video games can improve cognitive function in children.
- Video games can enhance spatial reasoning skills, working memory, attention, and processing speed.
- Playing video games regularly can also boost creativity and problem-solving abilities.
- However, excessive gaming can lead to negative effects such as addiction, sleep deprivation, and poor physical health.
